text: Kepala Island is one of outlying island of Indonesia. The island located in South China Sea, nortwest of Sarawak, East Malaysia. The island is part of Natuna Regency, and is the easternmost territory of Riau Islands province. The island is frequently visited by local fishermen for fishery purposes. At the center of the island there is a 30-meters high lighthouse, while the island itself is accessible by boat. == References == Category:Natuna Islands
title: Kepala Island
